1
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,920
Back then, when the masons were cutting into the mountain,

2
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:45,240
they discovered an ancient tomb during the blast.

3
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:47,320
Judging from the style of the ancient tomb,

4
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,520
it must be a grand tomb of a noble.

5
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:51,720
There were countless burial objects inside.

6
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:54,920
That Deputy Magistrate Cao insisted on going by himself.

7
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,800
And then?

8
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:58,800
Yeah.

9
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,520
At that time,

10
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,810
the main burial chamber was wide open.

11
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:09,520
It was full of gold and silver treasures buried with the dead.

12
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:11,520
It was absolutely dazzling.

13
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,640
At that moment, a shaman arrived.

14
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,600
She said they absolutely couldn't enter the tomb.

15
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:18,160
If anyone entered, they would surely face divine retribution.

16
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,760
But Cao Shaoyin refused to listen

17
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,690
and insisted on entering the tomb.

18
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,320
The shaman tried to stop him,

19
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:27,960
which made Cao Shaoyin fly into a rage.

20
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,520
He even sent many soldiers

21
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:34,079
to forcibly drag the shaman out of the tomb.

22
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:40,160
Cao Shaoyin led his men into the tomb.

23
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:43,400
After opening the coffin, strange things happened one after another,

24
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,000
and people kept dying.

25
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,800
Who among you here

26
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:56,880
entered the tomb with Cao Shaoyin?

27
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:02,040
I... I also went down into the tomb.

28
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,080
Me too.

29
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,280
So many people.

30
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,360
Yeah.

31
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,720
How strange.

32
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,000
Why did those few happen to be the ones who died?

33
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:23,640
That day, they were the first to dig to the tomb door,

34
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,600
and reported the matter to me.

35
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:30,880
Their actions must have angered the tomb owner,

36
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:33,579
causing them to suffer this misfortune.

37
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:40,040
He is Cao Shaoyin's younger brother.

38
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,800
We can't afford to offend him.

39
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,970
Alright, let me introduce him.

40
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,760
This is Military Advisor Cao.

41
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,400
He is Cao Shaoyin's younger brother

42
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:51,480
and also the chief supervisor for our quarrying operation.

43
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:52,640
Cao Fang.

44
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:04,160
Next to die from the curse was the Deputy Governor Cao.

45
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,600
According to his wife,

46
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:06,800
at noon every day,

47
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:10,040
the Deputy Governor would take a short nap after his meal.

48
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,560
When Cao Fang came to see him,

49
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:15,480
his wife went into the bedroom to wake him up.

50
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,519
But he had a dead look on his face,

51
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,920
and hung upside down.

52
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:32,320
Their deaths were all too strange.

53
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,880
Maybe it really was a curse.

54
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,520
Our opening the tomb must have angered the owner.

55
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,800
We shouldn't have dug it up.

56
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,320
I heard that in this kind of ancient tomb,

57
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,380
there are guardians at the entrance.

58
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,690
Those who break into the formation

59
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,250
will be punished by Heaven.

60
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,840
In that case,

61
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,520
we might as well try

62
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,360
going down the tomb to break the formation.

63
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,490
Going down the tomb?

64
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,800
This is my amulet.

65
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:17,520
I've never had an accident in so many years.

66
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,690
I'm giving it to you.

67
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,400
It will keep you safe.

68
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,680
Don't worry.

69
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,960
Let me put it on you.

70
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,620
Are we really going down the tomb?

71
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:12,600
Constable Qin, you can't pat people on the shoulder here.

72
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,120
It could be fatal.

73
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,160
What?

74
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,920
Do you really believe in curses that kill?

75
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,000
Otherwise, what?

76
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,560
Could someone have murdered them?

77
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,080
So far,

78
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:26,200
the first to die was the foreman

79
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,920
because he owed his subordinates wages

80
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,680
and had a dispute with them.

81
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,440
The ones who died later were all workers.

82
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:36,000
The last one was Junior Governor Cao.

83
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:37,680
He was advanced in years

84
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,120
and had no children,

85
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,880
but recently his young wife brought good news.

86
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,080
He was going to be a father in his old age.

87
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:46,320
He originally wanted to hold a banquet to celebrate,

88
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,480
but unexpectedly,

89
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:51,520
the happy event turned into a funeral.

90
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,880
The condition of their bodies currently appears to be consistent.

91
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,600
So we can now conclude

92
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,960
that the suspect is the same person.

93
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:03,480
But there's no connection between them at all.

94
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,280
Why would the suspect kill them?

95
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,720
Let's hurry back to the government office.

96
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,480
I think we need to sort out the clues again.

97
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,560
Right, we can't stay here long.

98
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:13,480
Alright.

99
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:14,760
Stop picking it up. Leave it.

100
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:15,880
This place isn't clean.

101
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,080
Ask Madam for another one. Okay?

102
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,240
Hurry up.

103
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:28,320
This incense bead was made by Mrs. Qin herself.

104
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:32,370
Although so many years have passed

105
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,040
and the fragrance is gone,

106
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:37,560
I still remember its size and color.

107
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:41,480
So, the grave robbers told the ghost market merchant

108
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:44,560
that they went through a lot of trouble to bring it out of the tomb

109
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,290
just to sell it for a good price.

110
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,240
And the tomb they robbed

111
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,760
is the princess's tomb you went to back then.

112
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,000
Yes.

113
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,960
Back then, all the burial objects in the tomb

114
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,840
were collected by the government

115
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:59,440
and sent to the Court of the Imperial Garrison in the capital for safekeeping.

116
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:03,760
Therefore, the tomb must be completely empty now.

117
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,320
Then how was the case solved back then?

118
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,800
And who was the suspect?

119
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,600
Why did he kill those people?

120
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:17,400
The trick the killer used is called

121
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:20,640
hiding a leaf in the forest.

122
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,040
What does that mean?

123
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,360
If you want to hide a leaf,

124
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,840
the best place

125
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,200
is in the forest.

126
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,400
If you want to cover up a murder motive,

127
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,559
the best way

128
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,320
is to kill more people.

129
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,960
At first, I didn't understand either,

130
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,200
why the suspect killed several people in a row

131
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,730
when the victims seemed entirely unrelated.

132
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:46,880
Actually, the suspect wanted to hide a leaf in the forest.

133
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:50,760
The real purpose was to kill Cao Shaoyin.

134
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,680
The rest of the murders

135
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,560
were just to cover up this real purpose.

136
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,000
And the only one who could do this

137
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,240
is you.

138
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:04,120
Cao Shaoyin is my own brother.

139
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,200
Why would I want to harm him?

140
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,500
Cao Shaoyin originally had no children,

141
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:13,080
so all his property would have been inherited by you.

142
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,680
But he had a son in his old age

143
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:17,520
and changed his mind under his wife's instigation.

144
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:20,000
You wanted to kill them after you found out.

145
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:23,240
Just when the ancient tomb was dug up while building the mountain road,

146
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:25,080
you came up with an idea.

147
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,160
You bribed the shaman

148
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,880
to spread rumors about the ancient tomb's curse,

149
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:32,280
while using the curse to kill them one by one

150
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:35,160
to minimize suspicion against you.

151
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,680
Nonsense.

152
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,200
Their strange deaths are... are what?

153
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,200
They were poisoned to death, weren't they?

154
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:42,960
Bo.

155
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:46,610
This is a colorless, odorless, and water-soluble Miao poison.

156
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,600
The poisoned person twitches all over and bends backward.

157
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:53,080
It's a rare and exotic poison.

158
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:55,840
I believe

159
00:09:56,640 --> 00:10:00,100
there should still be some of this Miao poison in your mansion.

160
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:03,400
To prove you're not the killer,

161
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:06,520
we just need to search your mansion.

162
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,920
Before we reached his bedroom,

163
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:11,920
Army Supervisor Cao drew his sword and killed himself.

164
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:16,080
Later, we found Miao poison under his bed.

165
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:18,560
After Vice Governor Cao died,

166
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,520
Miss,

167
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:24,760
your father was promoted from Recording Supervisor

168
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,080
to the position of Vice Governor.

169
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,280
Elder Su,

170
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,360
may I have a look at this incense bead?

171
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,360
Sure.

172
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,920
It's been so long.

173
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,560
The smell must be gone by now.

174
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,440
Dad, I really didn't expect

175
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:43,240
that you were involved in so many strange cases when you were young.

176
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,160
You

177
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,640
always underestimate your dad.

178
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:48,040
Let me tell you, the cases I participated in back in the day

179
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,440
were countless.

180
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:52,680
The riverside cruise ship murder case,

181
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,280
the Luoyang golden Buddha theft case,

182
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:58,200
and the thousand-year-old painting theft case,

183
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:01,480
were all solved by me and Constable Qin.

184
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,040
As long as you are interested,

185
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:06,640
I will slowly tell you about them in the future.

186
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:07,840
Okay.

187
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:10,360
I just remembered

188
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:12,080
I still have soup stewing at home.

189
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:12,720
Then go quickly.

190
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,040
Hurry up and go.

191
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,040
That's not right.

192
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:21,360
I came today to ask you about the theft involving the Guan family's youngest daughter.

193
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:23,520
How did it turn into a tomb-raiding case?

194
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:24,760
Ah, I'm so cold.

195
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,120
I'm going inside to put on a jacket. Can I wear yours?

196
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,480
Okay, go ahead.

197
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,120
It's freezing.

198
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,640
About that case, I...

199
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,640
I recently learned a new dish,

200
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,160
beef stew. I'm going to study it.

201
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:35,640
No,

202
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:36,200
we have enough to eat.

203
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,320
I need to use the restroom.

204
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,580
Su Lang, where are you running off to now?

205
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:41,760
These kids.

206
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,400
Another poor man's tomb.

207
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,360
Master.

208
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:16,400
Why didn't you let me crawl through the tunnel this time?

209
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:20,880
We only dig tunnels for you to crawl through in big tombs.

210
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:23,160
Poor men's tombs are buried shallow,

211
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,280
and easy to dig.

212
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,040
But there's not much money in it.

213
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,840
Not even a gold tooth.

214
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,400
Xiaobao, hurry and bring the bag.

215
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,360
Hurry up.

216
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,200
Come on, hurry.

217
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,200
Master!

218
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,520
There's treasure!

219
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,840
This is a huge treasure!

220
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,360
Keep up.

221
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,640
Oh no, someone's coming!

222
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:51,680
Xiaobao, go home first.

223
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,250
I'll distract them!

224
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,320
Run!

225
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,020
Don't move.

226
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,440
Bad guy.

227
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,520
Let me go.

228
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Let me go.

229
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:55,320
He's a fool.

230
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:57,000
I'm not a fool.

231
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:00,560
Let go.

232
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,760
Don't bite. Don't bite.

233
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,760
Let go.

234
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:06,760
Let go of me.

235
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,000
It's me. It's me, sister.

236
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:17,720
We lost them.

237
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:18,960
The routes in this area,

238
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,560
they are more familiar with.

239
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,400
I should have called more people.

240
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:25,680
But I was afraid of alerting them.

241
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:36,640
In this tomb,

242
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,320
why are there no bones?

243
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,720
It must have been stolen.

244
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,280
Stealing bones.

245
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,480
What's the use of that?

246
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:57,680
Come here.

247
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,680
Xia Zhiming.

248
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:07,360
Wife, Xia Chunyi.

249
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:10,760
This is the grave of the landlady's late husband.

250
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:12,000
The landlady?

251
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:16,840
This place is so desolate and overgrown with weeds.

252
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:20,280
No one has visited this grave for a long time.

253
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:22,720
Ever since the day I met her,

254
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,680
I have never heard her mention her husband.

255
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,880
I only knew that her marriage was unhappy.

256
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:30,740
She ran away from home and stayed in Yichun Brothel.

257
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:31,960
Later on.

258
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:33,880
She became the landlady.

259
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:38,240
So you first met her in Yichun Brothel?

260
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:39,080
Yes.

261
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,920
Don't go! Don't go!

262
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:43,840
You little brat.

263
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,400
Believe it or not, I'll beat you to death.

264
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,460
You stole something! You're a thief!

265
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,120
Did I steal from you?

266
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,120
You stole the oil seller's money.

267
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,120
I saw it.

268
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:57,160
Forget it. Let the child go.

269
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,280
Child, I won't.

270
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,120
He is the thief.

271
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:01,560
See if I don't beat you to death today! I... I...

272
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,120
Stop!

273
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:02,920
I...

274
00:17:04,280 --> 00:17:06,400
You're a grown man bullying a child here.

275
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,400
Aren't you ashamed?

276
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:08,359
Who are you?

277
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,000
None of your business.

278
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,400
Get lost.

279
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,960
You are causing trouble in front of my shop.

280
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,280
Believe it or not, I'll report to the authorities.

281
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:15,760
Yes, report to the authorities.

282
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,690
We must report to the authorities.

283
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:19,599
Come.

284
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:22,640
Why did he hit you?

285
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:24,480
He stole the old man's money.

286
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,800
The old man sells oil.

287
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:27,560
The money he works hard to earn every day,

288
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:28,520
once it passes through his hands,

289
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:29,680
will be stained with oil.

290
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,360
While ordinary people's money won't have oil on it.

291
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,160
Makes sense.

292
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,560
If you really didn't steal the old man's money,

293
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,400
do you dare to take out all your copper coins

294
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,520
and soak them in water?

295
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:39,600
We'll know if there are oil stains once tested.

296
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,840
Yes, take them out and test them.

297
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,080
Test them. Test them.

298
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,080
Take them out and test them.

299
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,360
Fine, test them.

300
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:54,560
We should have stopped him just now.

301
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,120
Eat slowly.

302
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,960
What's your name, and how old are you?

303
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,440
Jueming, 12 years old.

304
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,370
Where are your parents?

305
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:12,240
They are both gone.

306
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,520
Then where do you live?

307
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,290
My mother mortgaged the house.

308
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,680
The pawnbroker took it away.

309
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:24,240
I took my luggage and lived in a temple.

310
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,120
I look for work everywhere.

311
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,480
What can you do?

312
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:34,440
Wash dishes, cook, wash and dry clothes.

313
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,160
I can do it all.

314
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,240
I can also gather herbs.

315
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:39,100
My mother used to be a pharmacist.

316
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,400
Why don't you stay here and do chores for me?

317
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,640
But I just took over this place.

318
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:51,320
I can't pay you much.

319
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,720
But I can provide you with food and a place to live.

320
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,680
Are you willing?

321
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,640
I am.

322
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,840
Thank you, boss.

323
00:18:57,520 --> 00:19:00,280
Don't call me boss, call me Sister Chunyi.

324
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,560
Sister Chunyi.

325
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:03,160
Eat.

326
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,320
The girls at Yichun Brothel

327
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:15,480
are mostly homeless.

328
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,200
She kindly took them in.

329
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:19,890
Such a loyal and affectionate person,

330
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:22,400
yet she never mentions her late husband.

331
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,520
She must have her difficulties.

332
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:30,880
The boss must have set up this tomb herself.

333
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:33,280
Now that her late husband's tomb has been robbed,

334
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,720
I must tell her.

335
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,760
As for those two thieves,

336
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,960
we must bring them to justice.

337
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:46,040
Pastries. Sweet and fragrant pastries.

338
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:48,140
- I'll take one.
- Alright, two coins.

339
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:50,960
Two coins.

340
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,440
Alright.

341
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,640
Take care.

342
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,040
What do you want?

343
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:58,400
This one? Two coins.

344
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,680
Two coins. Two coins.

345
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:05,980
Where is the money?

346
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,880
Go away, you idiot.

347
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:11,160
Seriously.

348
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:14,000
Don't ruin my business. Get lost.

349
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,680
Watch your mouth.

350
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:17,720
Are you...

351
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,640
I didn't know the child was yours.

352
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,760
Please forgive my offense.

353
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,520
- Wrap it up.
- Alright.

354
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,600
Here, young master, take it.

355
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:29,720
This one. And this one too.

356
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,440
- Wrap it up.
- OK.

357
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,040
What a snob.

358
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,720
- Take care.
- Let's go, Xiaobao.

359
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:38,520
OK.

360
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,040
Xiaobao.

361
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,920
You know, just reaching out your hand is useless.

362
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:48,040
You also have to say, Pan Lang is my master.

363
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:49,880
Then they will give you food.

364
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,440
Pan Lang is my master.

365
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:55,120
That's right. Eat.

366
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,640
Is it good?

367
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,560
Master, you eat too.

368
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:04,120
I won't eat. You eat, Xiaobao.

369
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,520
I have money now.

370
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:08,360
I can take you to a restaurant for roast chicken.

371
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:13,920
When you get to the restaurant, just yell, Pan Lang is my master.

372
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,120
Who said my Xiaobao is silly?

373
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:18,320
My Xiaobao is not silly at all.

374
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:21,120
Let's go play a few games first.

375
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:23,120
Make some more money, okay?

376
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,000
Yeah.

377
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:24,800
Let's go.

378
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,240
Panlang is my master.

379
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,880
Panlang is my master.

380
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,520
Panlang is my master.

381
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:38,440
Panlang is my master.

382
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:43,240
Mr. Zhou, it's been a while.

383
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:44,920
Boss.

384
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:46,160
Have you forgotten all about me?

385
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:47,640
How could I?

386
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,200
Quick, we have good seats inside. Right this way.

387
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,000
Please.

388
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:50,720
Okay.

389
00:21:50,760 --> 00:21:51,400
Right this way, sir.

390
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,520
Chunyi.

391
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,000
You brat.

392
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,370
Finally remembered to visit me today.

393
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,880
I've been too busy lately,

394
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:58,640
but I dream of you often.

395
00:21:58,640 --> 00:21:59,720
Such a smooth talker.

396
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,960
You always know what to say.

397
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:03,200
Miss Li, Constable Su, please come in. This way.

398
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,040
Right this way.

399
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,440
Bring out all of Jueming's favorite dishes.

400
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,120
Bring extra portions. Sure thing.

401
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:06,920
Just a moment.

402
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,200
Let's go.

403
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:10,000
How have you been lately?

404
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:10,640
I'm doing well,

405
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,880
just a bit tired.

406
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,440
This new belt is nice.

407
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:19,120
Boss Zhou got some new fabrics,

408
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,760
so I made some clothes for the girls.

409
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:23,400
There were some scraps left over, and I didn't want to waste them,

410
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,000
so I made a belt.

411
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:32,080
Chunyi, was your late husband's name Xia Zhiming?

412
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,800
Yes.

413
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:34,840
Why do you ask?

414
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:38,600
Here's the thing.

415
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:42,360
Last night, we found his coffin in the eastern suburbs cemetery had been robbed.

416
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,160
Were there any valuable burial objects inside?

417
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,120
Burial objects?

418
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:50,600
No.

419
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,620
Our family was poor back then,

420
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:54,700
so there weren't any burial objects.

421
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,480
That's strange.

422
00:22:57,680 --> 00:23:00,360
When we found the coffin, it was completely empty.

423
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:02,240
Even the bones were stolen.

424
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,440
Even the bones are gone?

425
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:08,320
Were there any valuable items worn on the bones?

426
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,040
Definitely not.

427
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:14,520
Then in the dead of night,

428
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:18,080
what use would a grave robber have for a pile of bones?

429
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:20,960
Could he be a necrophiliac?

430
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:23,640
Don't talk nonsense.

431
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,040
Just guessing.

432
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:25,960
A guess.

433
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,680
Don't worry, Chunyi.

434
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:32,920
We will definitely bring these grave robbers to justice.

435
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,280
It's fine.

436
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:36,360
There's nothing valuable in the coffin.

437
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:37,720
It doesn't matter if it's lost.

438
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:40,520
I've forgotten about this person long ago.

439
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:42,120
Come have some snacks.

440
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,920
This is osmanthus cake made by Sister Chunyi herself.

441
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:47,960
Try our signature dish.

442
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,840
Place your bets! Big! Big! Big!

443
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:52,440
Hurry up! Quick!

444
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,320
Bet! Place your bets!

445
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:55,840
Small! Small!

446
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:57,480
Again.

447
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,320
Again.

448
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:04,280
Place your bets.

449
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:05,320
Bet big or small.

450
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:07,800
I don't believe it won't be big.

451
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:11,320
All in on big! Big! Big!

452
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,200
Reveal!

453
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:17,920
Continue.

454
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:19,840
Place your bets.

455
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,000
Bet big or small.

456
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,400
I'll bet small this time.

457
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:28,920
Little goldfish.

458
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:33,040
Don't you have a mother either?

459
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:41,600
You said your mother is in the water.

460
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,600
I'll send you to find your mother.

461
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:55,960
Come back often.

462
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:57,800
Welcome to Yichun Pavilion. Come back often.

463
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,040
Cheers.

464
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,280
Chunyi, the bill.

465
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:03,920
Madam.

466
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:05,120
Come back often.

467
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,480
Madam.

468
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,360
Coming.

469
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,200
I'll go say hello.

470
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,240
Oh.

471
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:16,320
Pan, you really come here morning and night.

472
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:19,240
I've been missing the boss lady day and night.

473
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,920
A day apart feels like three years.

474
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:23,890
Let's go upstairs and talk.

475
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:27,440
You guys go ahead and eat.

476
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:30,760
Come.

477
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,400
Mingzhu.

478
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:37,400
What's wrong?

479
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,280
Who exactly is this person

480
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:42,140
that the boss lady would personally entertain him?

481
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,880
I'm not exactly sure either.

482
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,880
I just know he's a cloth merchant.

483
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:48,840
He used to come by occasionally for a drink.

484
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:51,160
Mingzhu.

485
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:53,640
Please get me another portion of this pastry.

486
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,570
Coming right up!

487
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:05,650
Is the osmanthus cake good?

488
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:06,840
It is.

489
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:08,840
Let's save one for Brother Sulang later.

490
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:09,800
Yeah.

491
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,960
Hold out your hand.

492
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:23,240
Sister Chunyi said we can't just take money from others.

493
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,280
We can't take this.

494
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:24,840
Right.

495
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,400
Chunyi is right.

496
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:29,600
We really shouldn't just take things from others.

497
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:30,880
But this

498
00:26:30,960 --> 00:26:32,420
isn't given for no reason.

499
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:36,320
I know you've had a hard life since you were little.

500
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:37,520
This

501
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:41,920
is a reward I prepared for your bravery.

502
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:43,680
Take it.

503
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:46,200
In the future, if you face difficulties

504
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,800
or need help,

505
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,840
you can protect yourselves better.

506
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:51,960
Thank you.

507
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:55,000
Thank you. You're welcome.

508
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:58,040
Ma'am, don't forget.

509
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:59,040
I'll be waiting for you.

510
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,440
Don't worry.

511
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:01,680
Come, take your time.

512
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,680
Take care.

513
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,560
Take care. Mr. Li, take care.

514
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:05,640
Sister Chunyi.

515
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:07,960
Jueming.

516
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:11,520
As for that grave robber,

517
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:14,280
we'll let you know as soon as we have news.

518
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,400
We'll be going now. Let's go.

519
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:17,640
Don't go.

520
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,720
There's a Candlelight Dance tonight.

521
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:22,360
You've seen it, but these two haven't.

522
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:24,130
What is the Candlelight Dance?

523
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:26,480
You'll find out in a bit.

524
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,160
How is it?

525
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,200
It's really nice.

526
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,240
Where did this dance come from? I've never seen it.

527
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:30,600
Sister Chunyi created this dance herself.

528
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:33,120
It uses candles as a guide, lighting or extinguishing them

529
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:35,400
to create an atmosphere of alternating light and dark.

530
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,280
The audience

531
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:40,320
can see the dancers constantly shuttling between light and dark.

532
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,480
Interesting, right?

533
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,960
It's really nice.

534
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:51,080
In ancient times, there was the magnificent Nishang Yuyi Dance,

535
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:53,400
and the elegant Jinghong Dance.

536
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:56,160
I've seen the passionate Huxuan Dance,

537
00:28:56,200 --> 00:29:00,520
but I never imagined the magical Candlelight Dance.

538
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,800
It's truly fantastic.

539
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,600
I'm glad you like it.

540
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:07,080
I really enjoyed drinking today.

541
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,200
It was great.

542
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,760
Let's do it again next time.

543
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:10,720
Okay.

544
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:12,440
What's that?

545
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,480
Why is there a pair of shoes?

546
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:16,600
What's in the water?

547
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,120
It's a person.

548
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:23,320
It really is a person.

549
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:33,440
Okay.

550
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:44,280
Pan, who was just here, died by the moat.

551
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,240
What?

552
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:48,600
Thank you all for coming tonight.

553
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,680
Be careful. There is a step here.

554
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,400
How did you two find the body?

555
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,520
My lord.

556
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:23,600
Zhang and I were drinking in a tavern.

557
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:26,640
On our way back, we found someone in the water.

558
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:32,200
There is a small amount of silt in the corpse's mouth and nasal cavity.

559
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:36,360
The silt is attached to the inside of the nasal cavity and between the lips and teeth.

560
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:38,680
There is a small amount of fluid in the mouth.

561
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:41,600
It was likely inhaled while struggling after falling into the water.

562
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:43,720
Su Lang, come help me.

563
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,300
Turn the body over.

564
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,720
There is a distinct wound on the back of the head.

565
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:54,520
The wound is irregular in shape.

566
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,280
There are abrasions around it.

567
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:59,040
The surrounding hair is matted with blood.

568
00:30:59,080 --> 00:31:01,140
It is suspected to be the fatal wound.

569
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:04,120
Blood is also oozing from the ear canal.

570
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:06,760
Let's check the rest of the body.

571
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:10,440
There are abrasions on the hands.

572
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:13,080
They were likely caused by scraping against underwater rocks

573
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,680
and other debris after falling into the water.

574
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:19,000
Rigor mortis is present,

575
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:22,240
initially showing in the jaw and neck.

576
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:24,120
The livor mortis is light red.

577
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:27,520
Time of death is less than two hours ago.

578
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:30,120
I remember when the proprietress saw Pan off,

579
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:32,040
we were also getting ready to leave.

580
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:34,160
She pulled us to watch the candlelight dance.

581
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:37,800
That was about two hours ago.

582
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,640
For a body recovered from the water,

583
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:47,600
there are four possible causes of death.

584
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:50,800
The first is natural drowning.

585
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:54,600
The second is being forced underwater and drowning.

586
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:57,760
The third is being thrown into the water after death.

587
00:31:58,160 --> 00:32:02,080
The fourth is falling into the water after a fatal injury.

588
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:05,160
Generally, for natural drowning victims,

589
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:07,440
there is a lot of mud in the nose and mouth,

590
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:09,280
and dirt under the fingernails.

591
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:11,360
This is caused by struggling and grabbing.

592
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:13,440
So we can rule out the first possibility.

593
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:15,600
This is a homicide.

594
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:17,560
If the body was dumped after death,

595
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:19,800
the chest appears relatively flat.

596
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:22,160
When pressed, there's no obvious fluctuation of fluid.

597
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,200
But his whole body

598
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,440
is edematous.

599
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:29,480
Thus, he fell into the water while still breathing

600
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:31,780
and struggled for a while before he died.

601
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,840
At this hour,

602
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:38,700
the suspect had to keep the victim pressed in the water.

603
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:41,520
Wasn't he afraid of being seen?

604
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:48,920
Is it possible that he was drowned elsewhere

605
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,940
and then his body was dumped here?

606
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:54,400
If he was forced into the water to suffocate,

607
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,840
there would be petechiae in the victim's eyes.

608
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,200
But he doesn't have any,

609
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:01,600
and there are no choke marks on his neck.

610
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:03,440
There are no signs of pressure either.

611
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:05,300
And no scratch marks on the hands.

612
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:09,160
That leaves only one last possibility.

613
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:11,360
The victim suffered a fatal injury

614
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:12,960
and then fell into the water and died.

615
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:16,000
The suspect first invited Pan to the river,

616
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:20,320
then caught him off guard and hit his head with a rock,

617
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:22,690
causing him to fall into the water and die.

618
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:23,880
Be careful.

619
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:06,040
The soles are dry.

620
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,800
It seems before he fell into the water,

621
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:10,639
his shoes had already come off naturally.

622
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,920
The smell of the mud on the soles

623
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:15,050
perfectly matches the mud from the mountain graveyard.

624
00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:26,250
Stepping on a yellow talisman.

625
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:27,320
What is this?

626
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:27,679
Edict.

627
00:34:27,679 --> 00:34:30,440
This is a method used by grave robbers

628
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:32,320
to ward off evil when exploring yin tombs.

629
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:35,440
It seems he is the grave robber we are looking for.

630
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:37,000
He's dead just like that?

631
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,239
Little Mouse knows him.

632
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:41,520
Let's go ask him.

633
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:58,140
Come here. Why are you standing so far? Come take a look.

634
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:05,880
Get closer.

635
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:10,400
Yes, that's him.

636
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:13,120
He sold a lot of things at my place.

637
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,880
How did he get murdered?

638
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:18,880
What about the kid he usually brings along?

639
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:21,040
Do you know where he is now?

640
00:35:22,040 --> 00:35:23,680
Do you know who killed him?

641
00:35:23,720 --> 00:35:25,280
I don't know.

642
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:29,520
You don't know anything.

643
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:31,800
I don't know why you are here.

644
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:36,320
I found a bag of money this morning.

645
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,640
Is it yours?

646
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:39,880
Yes, yes, it's mine.

647
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,360
Yes, it's mine.

648
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:47,720
I even saw him this morning.

649
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,040
Go on.

650
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:52,920
He was gambling at Yabao Wang's place.

651
00:35:52,920 --> 00:35:55,250
He was extremely generous with his money.

652
00:35:58,440 --> 00:35:59,880
I told you to bet big.

653
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:03,120
Haozi, Haozi.

654
00:36:03,480 --> 00:36:04,320
Haozi.

655
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:05,800
Don't go, Haozi.

656
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:07,000
Come back, Haozi.

657
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:09,600
Haozi, why are you running?

658
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:10,800
Give me some money.

659
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,680
Money.

660
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,680
I haven't made a single sale today.

661
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,440
How much did you lose?

662
00:36:18,720 --> 00:36:20,120
Where did you get the money?

663
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:20,960
Just don't ask.

664
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:21,920
I can definitely pay you back.

665
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:24,320
No wonder you're so generous today.

666
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:26,120
Where did you strike it rich?

667
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,160
Let me tell you.

668
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:30,920
I went grave robbing again yesterday.

669
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,520
I cracked open a large coffin.

670
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:35,050
There were some truly valuable items inside.

671
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:36,120
Give me some today.

672
00:36:36,120 --> 00:36:38,360
I promise to pay you back with interest.

673
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,280
I don't have any money.

674
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,840
But I know the Gambling King.

675
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,280
I can take you to get some credit.

676
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:47,280
Don't forget what you promised.

677
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:48,360
Let's go.

678
00:36:48,400 --> 00:36:49,240
I haven't made a sale.

679
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:50,760
I know the Gambling King.

680
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:52,080
Okay.

681
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,320
Did he really say that?

682
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:55,280
Of course.

683
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:58,640
I swear I didn't get a single word wrong.

684
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,160
So you lent it to him?

685
00:37:01,200 --> 00:37:03,000
I didn't, but...

686
00:37:03,040 --> 00:37:05,800
I introduced him to the Gambling King for credit.

687
00:37:06,040 --> 00:37:07,680
But he lost again.

688
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:08,780
This Gambling King

689
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:10,480
took the fool as a hostage

690
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,450
and ordered him to go get the money.

691
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:13,600
Xiaobao.

692
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:19,000
Xiaobao, go with this man later.

693
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:23,560
Master lost money.

694
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,130
I need to go find some money.

695
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,960
You stay here as collateral for now.

696
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:29,560
Understand?

697
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:33,600
Is that kid the hostage?

698
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:35,680
Yes.

699
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:40,640
I don't think Pan Lang would use money to redeem a fool.

700
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:43,760
Sir, you don't know this.

701
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:46,520
This fool is very important to Pan Lang.

702
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:49,720
Forming a team for tomb raiding is crucial.

703
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:51,600
Usually, it's either brothers

704
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:53,000
or a father and son.

705
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:54,600
One holds the rope outside,

706
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:55,840
while the other digs the hole.

707
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:57,480
If the hole is small,

708
00:37:57,600 --> 00:38:00,080
Pan Lang lets the fool go in.

709
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:02,560
If the tomb is complicated,

710
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:04,640
Pan Lang goes down himself.

711
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:08,520
He knows this fool is not greedy and values loyalty.

712
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:10,960
He won't just pull the treasure up

713
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:13,760
and let go of the safety rope.

714
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,380
Where is the Betting King?

715
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:17,720
I really don't know.

716
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,560
I've told you everything I know.

717
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:35,600
Didn't I tell you?

718
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:39,300
Don't bother me these days if it's nothing. Don't you understand?

719
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:43,440
Chunyi.

